inn1.comm: lifting delivery on the rib cage, fended away in an ungainly fashion but hey he will get some runs as the ball rolls behind square-leg
and follows that good delivery with a wide. Typical West Indies. Inconsistent.
well outside off and Voges goes chasing it but can't get wood on leather.
outside off stump line, steered to point
fullish outside off stump, Voges edges the intended drive to the off side and off they rush across for a quick single
short in length, on the middle and leg iine, dabbed to the on side for yet another quick single
full and well outside off stump, left alone
full in length outside off stump, left alone
leans across to push the length delivery to cover
way wide outside off stump ...
closer to the off stump, goes through the channel, left alone
short in length, kicking up with bounce, left alone
drifts to the pads and that has been glanced away to the fine-leg boundary
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
short in length ,moves into the middle, pushed away to the on side
lovely delivery, full in length, moves away from a length, away from the off stump, away from the outside edge
length delivery that cuts back in, Paine goes back to jab it away
full in length and outside off stump, left alone
Fabulous cover drive. Full pitched outside off stump line and Paine showcases his new bat with a yummy little cover drive
length delivery in the corridor, left alone
tip and run. Pushed to the on side and off they go.
leans across, coves the off stump before shouldering arms
Fine delivery. It lands on a length around off and curves away. Nice bounce and carry.
but drifts to the pads this time, glanced away for a single
around the off stump line, tapped to the off side, they think about a single but kill that thought
kicks up from short of length outside off, left alone
length delivery on the middle, tapped to the on side
length delivery straightening on the middle, defended to the on side
short in length outside off stump, cut away to third man
leans forward and across to defend to the off side
bounces from short of length, Voges' footwork is iffy on this occasion and he stabs it off the outer edge past the slip cordon
Nagging line and length outside off stump, left alone
leans forward to defend to the off side
way wide outside off stump and the keeper collects
lands full in length outside off and seams away with bounce, left alone
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
on a length, on the middle, little bit of seam movement is on offer, clipped behind square-leg
short and climbing outside off stump, Paine flashes it over the slip cordon
short in length and outside leg stump, left alone
around the off stump line, straightening a touch, poked out to the off side
short and climbing outside off, pushed out to point
mistimes the fullish delivery back to the bowler
Clatterrr!  It was a good incutter, cut in from the off and middle line, Paine tried to play it across the line, ended up playing all around it and lost his middle stump
full in length outside off stump, ;left alone
length delivery on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
short in length outside off stump line, punched away to point
another wide outside off stump
length delivery on the middle stump line, turned to the on side
Trapped in front! Goes for the yorker, it dipped in full and late, Voges thrust his front foot forward and yorked himself in the process. He was hit on the boot in front of middle stump. Gone!
cuts in with bounce, from outside off stump - there is definitely something in the track for the seamers - left alone
outside off stump, left alone
lands on a length outside off stump and moves away further, left alone
short in length at the body, goes for the pull, doesn't quite connect well and the ball rolls away to fine-leg region
shout for lbw but missing leg stump. It moved in from the middle stump line, Clarke was beaten by the movement, hopped back and pushed at it desperately ..
gets back and across to defend to the on side
jumps back and across towards off stump to defend to the off side
moves back again and clips an in cutter on the middle stump line to fine-leg
full and swinging away, Ponting shoulders arms
full in length and outside off stump, left alone
leans forward, taps the length delivery to the on side, thinks about a single but decides against it
outswinger outside off stump, square driven straight to point where Sammy makes a complete mess of it . Oh well ...
short and down the leg side, Ponting goes for the pull but doesn't connect
short in length outside off, punched away past point
Another wide from West Indies. It's been that kind of a day
Wide no 9.
stays back to punch a back-of-length delivery to cover
goes back and across, gets cramped for room as he gets too close to the ball and manages to jab it away in the end
short in length, outside off stump, punched away
full in length, cuts in from just outside off stump, Ponting lunges across to defend and inside edges on to the pad
outside off stump line, short in length and some width on offer, Ponting is slightly late in  deciding to pull out from a forcing shot, has a lazy waft and the ball flies past the blade
another one that seams back in on this spicy track, Clarke pushes across, falls over a bit and is hit on the pad .. going down leg, though
lovely delivery, cuts back in from outside off stump and rushes through the bat and pad gap .. comprehensively beaten
full and outside off stump, guided to backward point region
length delivery around off stump line, defended to the off side
full pitched and Ponting smashes it in the air past Smith who tries to "catch" it but the ball is too fast for him.
Another misfield. outside off stump, punched straight to cover where Deonarine makes an unholy mess of it.
walks right across the stumps, gets outside off and defends
Yet another wide. The track is helping the seamers but West Indies haven't been consistent with their lines and lengths so far
full in length, closer to the off stump, left alone
walks across and forward, gets close to the line of a length delivery outside off and pushes it to mid-off for a quick single
short in length outside off stump, steered to third man
short in length outside off, punched off the back foot , down to wide third man
full in length around the off stump line, pushed to mid-on
short in length outside off stump, punched away to sweeper cover
Crunchy! Smith bowls it short and Ponting rocks back to play an dismissive pull shot
And Guess what .. Wide No 11. Way way outside off
length delivery around off stump line, defended on the front foot
length delivery outside off, tapped back down the pitch
fullish, on the middle, on driven through midwicket
outside off stump, moving away, guided down to third man
Clarke walks down the track and across.. gets outside off stump and leaves this delivery ... Ponting walks down the track for a chat with his partner
back of length around off stump line, pushed away to short cover
walks down the track, again gets outside off, and chases a wide one but misses it
fetches the length delivery from the off stump line and flicks it past square-leg
moves forward to flick a full delivery from the off and middle line through midwicket
cuts in from outside off stump, Clarke is all around the crease and in the end stabs it away
jumps back to punch the short-of-length delivery to sweeper cover
full delivery, very full, whipped away to deep midwicket
length delivery around the off stump line, Ponting lunges across in in his inimitable fashion to push it to point
the slow bouncer ,, Ponting is too early into his pull shot and Pollard has a big smile
yet another slow delivery, this time fuller around off stump, Ponting opens the bat-face to run it down to third man
tries the short one against  pup who punches to sweeper cover
on the middle and leg line, tapped cautiously to the on side of the pitch
on the middle and leg again, turned to the on side
walks down the track again, full delivery,  a slow off cutter like thingy, worked past square-leg from the middle stump line ..
outside off stump, shaping in a bit, Ponting hangs on the back foot to run it down to third man
gets forward to drive through covers
fuller, on the off stump line, driven to mid-on
short in length outside off stump, punched away to point
slower one outside off stump, steered away to third man

ha! loverly drama out there. It was the short delivery, Ponting was too early into his pull shot.. the ball ran off his thigh pad towards the middle stump and Ponting sort of chopped it like cutting a piece of wood with an axe ..
outside off stump line, run past point
full in length outside off, guided to backward point where there is a fumble
short in length outside off, punched away to point
length delivery outside off stump, pushed away to backward point
short in length outside off stump, dabbed down to third man

Is it Ponting or some Indian cricketer out there?! Hopping and skipping and jumping against short deliveries. It was a short-of-length delivery on the middle stump line, Ponting is on the hop and tries to stab it away desperately and is hit on the thigh pad

And he is a goner now! Full in length, outside the off stump and that change of length has worked like a charm. Ponting is late in getting forward, sort of lunges out at the last minute and pushes outside the line. The ball collides with the inner edge and crashes into the stumps.
full in length and outside off stump, steered down to third man
short in length around off stump line, pushed out to mid-off
short and climbing outside off stump, left alone
leans forward to defend the length delivery on the off side
moves in to the middle stump line, defended to the off side
on a length outside off, left alone
cuts in from short of length on the middle, tapped gently to the on side of the pitch
length delivery from wide of the crease, defended to the leg side
full delivery outside off stump, driven towards long-off for a single
floated full outside off, tries to paddle sweep but misses
leans forward to defend to the off side
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
full in length around off stump line, nudged down to third man
length delivery around off stump line, on driven to mid-on
short and wide and cut away to sweeper cover
short in length outside off stump, defended on the front foot
full and well outside off stump, White goes for a big drive but doesn't connect
steered past point for a single
leans forward to push it towards mid-off for a single
short in length on the middle and leg, tapped behind square-leg
on the leg stump line, tapped to short midwicket
full and outside off, driven to long-off
moves down the track and pushes it back to the bowler
backs away but mistimes the cut to cover point
outside off stump, punched to right of sweeper cover
short in length, kicking up down the leg side, White tries to play the leg glance and I think it brushed the waist. "Love Handles," says Ian Healy. Oh well. I am not going there.
short and wide, slammed hard to right of short cover where Gayle makes a fine diving stop
length delivery on the middle stump, turned to the on side
fullish, on the off and middle stump line, on driven to long-on
length delivery outside the off stump, straightens out and White is beaten, pushing inside the line
floated on the middle, pushed down the track
skips down the track and pushes the ball to the off side
slightly short in length ,cut away to sweeper cover
floated just outside off, goes for the paddle sweep and is struck on the pad
slower, on the middle and off line, tapped to the off side
leans forward to defend to the off side
short in length, cut away to deep cover
short in length outside off stump, punched away to short cover
length delivery outside off stump, left alone
length delivery on the middle, turned to midwicket
short and outside off, forced away to deep cover
turns this one to right of midwicket for a single
turns away from the off stump, Clarke backs away but is beaten by the turn and mistimes the cut
straighter one, on the off stump line, pushed away to cover
beaten on the cut. Arm-ball outside off, Clarke goes for the cut but the ball bounces over the blade
cuts this one to sweeper cover
leans forward to defend to the bowler
floated full around off, driven to long-off
short in length, White goes for the pull, top edges it clear of midwicket fielder .. mid-on was deep near the boundary and had been there an conventional one, it could well have been caught.
leans forward to defend to the on side
gets forward to push a length delivery to the off side
fuller, around off, driven to Chris Gayle at short cover
from wide of the crease, slower one, Clarke moves down the track and on drives to long-on
short in length, punched past the bowler
full in length outside off, jabbed away
leans forward to flick the full delivery to short midwicket
goes back to swat it past square-leg
skips down the track to ping long-on
on the middle, goes on with the arm, pushed back down the track, it was briefly in the air but no danger
gets forward to drive to long-off
Got him! Caught him! Short in length and outside off stump, bit of extra bounce, White goes for the big cut but ends up nicking it behind. Australia wobbling a bit.
from round the stumps, full in length on the off stump line, defended back down the pitch
full in length, outside off stump line, left alone
length delivery around off stump line, tapped to the off side
slower one, from outside off stump, turned to midwicket
leans forward to push-drive to the off side
moves down the track and drives to the on side
on the middle and off line, worked to short midwicket
quicker one, short in length, skids on, pulls it away
from just outside off stump, steered to backward point
leans forward to push it past point
moves down the track to on drive to short mid-on fielder
from round the stumps, length delivery outside off stump, gently pushed to gap in cover region
length delivery on the off stump line, defended down the track
walks around the crease, almost gets outside off and on drives through mid-on
loopy slow bouncer .. Hussey tries to dab it to the off side and is beaten
Nice. Hussey leans forward to cream a full delivery through covers
outside off stump, from a length, run down to third man
gets forward to play the reverse paddle sweep
turns it behind square-leg for a single
pushes this one to extra cover
turns to the leg stump line, turned behind square-leg for yet another single
moves down the track to off drive to long-off
hangs back to push this one through point
stays back to clip this one off his pads
leans forward to play a compact looking defensive stroke
full and outside off, Hussey goes for the drive but gets an inside edge
Clarke walks down the track, the bowler shortens the length and gets to kick it up, Clarke just about manages to stab it through to third man but runs really hard to come back for the second run
takes couple of steps down the track and short-arm pulls it past square-leg
slower one from round the stumps, pushed to extra cover
moves down the track and drives to long-off
outside off stump, Hussey goes for the off drive but is beaten by the lack of spin
gets forward to ping long-on
on the off stump line, defended to cover
skips down the track to on drive through midwicket
floated full on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
length delivery on the middle and leg, clipped off the pad
slower one from round the stumps, Hussey adjusts to push it back to the bowler
slow again, outside off stump, full in length, Hussey waits on the front foot and drives through cover
moves down the track and drives past the bowler who tries to stop it with his right boot but doesn't ...
off cutter on the middle and leg, tapped to fine-leg region
short in length from round the stumps, Hussey pulls it away rather crunchy little shot to deep midwicket
moves down the track to drive it back to the bowler
skips down the track but yorks himself in the process and just manages to dig it out in the end
leans forward to turn it past midwicket
unfurls that reverse paddle sweep again - he doesn't play the normal revers sweep but sort of paddles it around to fine-leg
moves down the track and deflects it straight to short midwicket
leans across to drive through the off side
Sammy takes out pup. Clarke goes dancing down the track for a big hit but can only manage to play an ugly swipe across the line as Sammy, cleverly, shortened the length. Edge and gone!
bouncing delivery from short of length, at the body, runs away to short fine-leg region
full in length, squeezed out behind squaer-leg
leans forward to push it wide of midwicket
from round the stumps, length delivery around off, pushed away to point
drags it short and Hussey pulls it to Smith at deep midwicket
gets forward to jab a full delivery back down the pitch
goes back to whip it to deep midwicket
goes back to punch it back to the bowler
on the middle stump line, turned to the on side
just outside off stump, pushed away to short extra cover
short in length, punched through covers
cuts in from just outside off, guided to point
length delivery that straightens on the middle stump line, Hopes is squared-up completely like Ramnaresh Sarwan and edges it to the off side
stays beside the line to punch this one to cover
slower one, outside off, short in length, forced away to sweeper cover
full in length, on the off stump line, guided to backward point
short and outside off, cracked away past point
leans forward to drive it back to the bowler
length delivery outside off stump, pushed to cover
leans forward to deflect the full delivery to midwicket
full delivery on the pads, Hussey plays a deft leg glance to collect a boundary
fullish, not quite a yorker but thereabouts, dug out past the bowler
cuts in from short of length, pushed back to the bowler
goes back to work it towards mid-on and Gayle rushes after it
turns in on the off stump line, worked to midwicket
leans forward to on drive to long-on
quicker one, from round the stumps on the off stump line, worked for a single to midwicket
Lashed away! full and well outside off, Hopes reaches out, goes down on his knee and flashes it away through point
leans forward to drive to cover
banged in short and Hussey swivels to pull it away
leans forward to on drive a full delivery
short in length, cuts in towards off stump line, stabbed back down the track
fuller, around off and middle stump line, driven hard down the ground
jaffa .. it kicked up from back of length, from around the off and middle stump line and it left a surprised Hussey who pushed inside the line
a tad fuller, a touch wider and Hussey goes in chase of it but is beaten
leans forward to force a short of length delivery to left of long-off
fuller, eased down to long-on .. they think about second but change their mind. Hopes goes across to have a chat with Hussey.
short in length, bounces, Hussey gets under the ball too much as he pulls but manages to get it wide of deep midwicket; he wants the second, Hopes doesn't.
full pitched, driven to left of long-off  and furious running between the wicket gets them two runs this time
banged in short, pulled away for a single
low full toss on the middle, pushed out to cover for a single

moves down the track and slices a slower to point. He rushes for the quick single and dives to get back in the crease. Ravi Rampaul too lunges to his right to collect the ball and knocks out the stumps in the process. A fine desperate street cricket/backyard cricket  on view there.
fullish, swung away across the line
short in length, outside off stump, Hussey waits before opening the bat-face and guiding the ball to left of short third man where Nikita makes a half-stop
moves down the track, takes it on full but doesn't put it away; just pushes to extra cover
not quite a yorker but almost there, pushed out through mid-off
skips down the track and whips the full delivery but again straight to midwicket.
short in length outside off stump, cut away past point
Run out chance missed. It was driven straight to cover and they ran for it but the throw was wide.
slower, lands outside leg stump, breaks in, Hussey with the big ugly swipe across the line, misses and is struck on the thigh pad.
fuller and Hopes drives down the ground

short in length on the stumps, Hopes goes for the good-old slog across the line, the bottom-hand comes off the handle in the process and the ball flies off the top edge but falls well clear of midwicket
Clatter! The stumps are in disarray. Full, straight and Hussey goes for the big swing over midwicket but ...
full in length and outside off, Hopes slashes it away to third-man boundary

Soft dismissal. Hopes flicked a full delivery straight to midwicket. He cleared the front leg and whipped across the line but straight to the fielder and he has a wry smile when he sees the end result
full and on the leg stump line, goes past the waft and rolls away off the pad
fullish on the middle stump line, turned through midwicket
low full toss around off stump line, punched through point
Knocked down! Full inswinging yorker goes past Hauritz's bat and crashes into the middle stump, the bails fly and Ravi Rampaul screams in joy.
full in length on the leg stump line, driven down to long-on
full pitched delivery on the off and middle, driven away towards long-on
on the leg and middle, tries to work it across the line, misses but collects a leg bye.
Nine down and West Indians are smiling. Johnson top-edges the pull shot and Pollard rushes in from the deep midwicket region to take a fine tumbling catch.
full in length, around the off stump line, driven to extra cover
yorker length, well almost there, dug out to the off side
fullish, on the middle and leg line, swung away past short fine-leg fielder. He sort of lapped it around the corner
He unfurls that shot again. It's a bottom-hand powered swat-pull ... Again he picked the length delivery from leg and middle and lapped it to fine-leg boundary
Wallop. He clears the front foot and slams a length delivery from the off-stump line to midwicket boundary
Thunderous Smack! Harris .. take a bow. Immense fun. He moved outside the leg stump line and gave it a good clean hit over long-on. Up ... up and over.
holes out to long-off. It was there to be hit, a length delivery outside off but he was hanging way back inside the crease and lunged out to hit towards long-off ...

inn2.comm: full and moving down the leg side ... wide
short in length, bounces past the off stump, Gayle shoulders arms ..
fires across a bouncer around off stump, Gayle sways away
more bounce ... flies down legside though and Paine leaps to get it back to earth
fuller, curving away from the off stump line, Gayle allows it to pass him
bounces into the rib cage, turned to backward square-leg

This one threatens to knock out Gayle. It flew at his face, Gayle couldn't get away from it or so it seemed before he ducked at the very last minute and the ball flew over the helmet and the keeper. Nasty delivery.
full and around the off stump line, defended to the off side
